{"slug": "commune", "root": "commune", "category": "act", "gloss": "to converse with spirits/nature", "definition": "To commune is to enter into shared, intimate contact with spirits, gods, or nature — to hold something in common with them, exchanging presence rather than commands. It differs from conjuring: to conjure is to summon and bind a spirit to one's will, whereas to commune is to join with it, a reciprocal opening toward the divine or the departed rather than a compulsion of it.", "history": "The root is Latin *communicare*, 'to share,' from *communis*, 'common' — the same root as *communion* and *community*, so communing with spirits is, at bottom, holding something in common with them. The turn is contemplative: in the Neoplatonic and theurgic tradition that shaped Renaissance magic, *theurgia* aimed precisely at *koinōnia*, Iamblichus's 'communion of the gods with men,' the soul's ascent to unmediated contact rather than the coercion of *goetia*. The fourteenth-century monk of Fanger's study claims to have communed with spirits for thirty years; Dee sought communion with angels. Sharing, not summoning, is the key. Magic's *Commune with Nature* and kin keep that gentler, joining sense.", "def_sources": [{"label": "RenaissanceMagicDB, s.v. theurgia (ritual ascent to communion with the divine)", "where": "RenaissanceMagicDB"}, {"label": "Meyer & Mirecki, Magic and Ritual in the Ancient World (theurgic communion of gods with men)", "where": "Renaissance magic (PDF)"}, {"label": "Fanger, Invoking Angels (communed with spirits for thirty years)", "where": "Medieval magic (PDF)"}, {"label": "Etymonline, s.v. commune", "where": "Etymology reference"}], "commentary": null, "commentary_sources": [], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"lang": "Latin", "origin": "Latin communicare 'to share' (communis 'common')", "first": "c. 1300", "note": "To commune with spirits is to hold something in common with them; the same root as communion and community.", "hook": "A séance is a kind of sharing."}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 3, "oracle_total": 0, "in_flavor_cards": 3, "in_oracle_cards": 0, "name_match_count": 9, "by_variant": {"commune": 2, "communing": 1}, "first_year": 2016, "colors": {"B": 2, "G": 7, "U": 1, "R": 2}, "by_year": {"2016": 1, "2021": 1, "2022": 3, "2023": 3, "2024": 1, "2025": 1, "2026": 2}}, "cards": [{"id": "6042a806-6e6a-4f1d-9563-5932a17f32f9", "name": "Commune with the Gods", "set": "EMA", "set_name": "Eternal Masters", "released": "2016-06-10", "type_line": "Sorcery", "rarity": "common", "colors": ["G"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/6/7/67d95f6f-3ff0-483d-b98f-ccb4fb5715f4.jpg?1782749851", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/6/7/67d95f6f-3ff0-483d-b98f-ccb4fb5715f4.jpg?1782749851", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/ema/162/commune-with-the-gods?utm_source=api", "local": "img/commune/6042a806-6e6a-4f1d-9563-5932a17f32f9.jpg"}, {"id": "f4aa0f64-d202-42a1-af62-0e53bbe87782", "name": "Commune with Lava", "set": "AFC", "set_name": "Forgotten Realms Commander", "released": "2021-07-23", "type_line": "Instant", "rarity": "rare", "colors": ["R"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/8/6/862771b6-8e82-45b7-922f-4f40322a607e.jpg?1782704135", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/8/6/862771b6-8e82-45b7-922f-4f40322a607e.jpg?1782704135", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/afc/118/commune-with-lava?utm_source=api", "local": "img/commune/f4aa0f64-d202-42a1-af62-0e53bbe87782.jpg"}, {"id": "68f8ed23-024e-414f-bbb2-ab73fbe21b69", "name": "Commune with Spirits", "set": "NEO", "set_name": "Kamigawa: Neon Dynasty", "released": "2022-02-18", "type_line": "Sorcery", "rarity": "common", "colors": ["G"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall